      "message": "looks like you\u0027re just splitting the string by a space character. What about android/base/misc/StringUtils.h, split():\n\nstd::vector\u003cstd::string\u003e splitArgs;\nandroid::base::split(args, \" \", [\u0026splitArgs](StringView s) { if (!s.empty()) splitArgs.push_back(s); });\n\nthis way you don\u0027t need to have a custom limit of the string length, won\u0027t use 16KB of stack space and don\u0027t limit the number of arguments",
